{"lemma":"فارِغ","slug":"فارِغ","root":"ف.ر.غ","root_slug":"ف-ر-غ","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-غ","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فارِغ","root":"فرغ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33649"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%BA"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of فَرَغَ or فَرِغَ (faraḡa or fariḡa).","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"empty","examples":[{"text":"إِنَاء فَارِغ","english":"an empty vessel"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"inane, vacuous, useless","examples":[{"text":"كَلَام فَارِغ","english":"idle talk"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of فَرَغَ (faraḡa, “to become empty”)."},"ipa":["/faː.riɣ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33649","headword_ar":"فَارِغٌ","root":"frg","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Empty, vacant, void, devoid, destitute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unoccupied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAlK","text_ar":"خَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaA='N fArigN","text_ar":"اـِنَا=ءٌ فارِغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an empty vessel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA:) and likewise applied to a man, (O, TA, *) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vacant"},{"kind":"text","text":"from,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid"},{"kind":"text","text":"of, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free"},{"kind":"text","text":"from, business, occupation, or employment; (K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farigN","text_ar":"فَرِغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K, TA:) [and often, used elliptically, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vacant from, devoid of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from, business"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"care"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anxiety"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquietude; unoccupied, unemployed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at leisure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforagu","text_ar":"اَفْرَغُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArigN","text_ar":"فَارِغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) as in the phrase, of Ru-beh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oguwlu mivolu AlA^aforagi","text_ar":"المَشْغُولُ مِثْلُ الاَفْرَغِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The busied is not like the free from business"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fur~aAgN","text_ar":"فُرَّاغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArigN","text_ar":"فَارِغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firogN","text_ar":"فِرْغٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fur~aAgN","text_ar":"فُرَّاغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K; [in the former, as is often the case, the sign of tesh-deed in this word has been carelessly omitted; and in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfragu","text_ar":"الفرَغُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfur~aAgu","text_ar":"الفُرَّاغُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and has been erroneously supposed to be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaraAgu","text_ar":"الفَرَاغُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) for ex., Tuleyhah Ibn-Khuweylid El-Asadee says, in relation to the slaying of his brother's son, Hibál Ibn-Selemeh Ibn-Khuweylid,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"famaA Zan~ukumo biAlqawomi A_i*o taqotuluwnahumo\n                      \n                     \n                        A^alayosuwA waA_ino lamo yusolimuwA birijaAli\n                      \n                     \n                        faA_ino taku A^a*owaAdN A^uSibona wanisowapN\n                      \n                     \n                        falano ta*ohabuwA firogFA biqatoli HibaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And what is your opinion of the party when ye slay them? Are they not"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though they have not become Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men? And if some small numbers of camels have been smitten"},{"kind":"text","text":"(and carried off)."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and some women, ye will not go away free from care by reason of the slaying of Hibál"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) It is said in the Kur [xxviii. 9],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^aSobaHa fw^aAdu A^um~i","text_ar":"وَاَصْبَحَ فوَادُ اُمِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwsaY faArigFA","text_ar":"مُوسَى فَارِغًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind, of the mother of Moses became devoid of patience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid of everything except remembering"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Moses: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid of anxiety;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of God's having promised to restore him to her, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2383},{"kind":"text","text":"by words in the next but one of the preceding verses. (O.) [See also another reading voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firogN","text_ar":"فِرْغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and another, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furugN","text_ar":"فُرُغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And it is said in a form of prayer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A_in~iY A^asoA^aluka AlEayo$i Alr~aAfigi waAlmaAla","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ اـِنِّى اَسْاَلُكَ العَيْشِ الرَّافِغِ وَالمَالَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaAriga","text_ar":"الفَارِغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, I ask of Thee ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant, and pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, means of subsistence, and cattle free from labour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN faArigN ma$oguwlN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فَارِغٌ مَشْغُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is devoted to that which is unprofitable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$gl","text_ar":"شغل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA kalaAmN faArigN","text_ar":"هٰذَا كَلَامٌ فَارِغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is empty talk"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"language"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","K"]}]}}